analysis.Extra Information:
• Bellampalli is an SC-reserved mining constituency located in Mancherial district.
• The area is known historically for coal mines and strong labour union influence.
• CPI won the very first (2009) election here — rare for Telangana constituencies.
• TRS/BRS held the seat for two consecutive terms (2014 & 2018).
• INC won in 2023 with ~57.96% vote share and ~36,878 majority — a major sentiment shift.
• Bellampalli is considered a wave seat because the ruling party changed in 2023.
• Workers issues, coal safety, and wage concerns strongly shape local politics.
• Significant presence of Singareni workers affects voting trends.
